{{Infobox ski area | name = Abondance Ski Valley | image =logo-abondance-ski.png | caption = Company logo | location = Abondance valley, [[Haute-Savoie]], [[Rhone-Alpes]], [[France]] | number_trails = 17 }}
'''Abondance Ski Valley''' is a mid-sized ski area in the [[Haute-Savoie]] region of France, near [[Châtel, Haute-Savoie|Châtel]] and La Chapelle d'Abondance. The resort has been open since at least 1964<ref name="pistehors">http://pistehors.com/news/ski/comments/0735-abondance-abandons-skiing/</ref> and was closed in 2007, when the local council voted to shut down the area after 15 years of loss-making.<ref name="pistehors" /> The resort was reopened, however, in 2009 when Gregory Lynn Sherwood, an American entrepreneur, made a deal with the local mayor to operate the ski area for the next 12 years.<ref>http://funinthealps.co.uk/abondance-ski-resort-is-reopening-after-two-years/</ref>
==Location== Abondance Ski Valley is located in the Abondance Valley, in the [[Chablais Alps]]. The resort is one of 12 ski stations in the [[Portes du Soleil]] linked ski area,<ref>http://en.portesdusoleil.com/</ref> and is open to Portes du Soleil combined ticket holders, however it is not linked to any other resorts and a drive to La Chapelle d'Abondance or Châtel is required in order to access the rest of the Portes du Soleil.
