{{Infobox venue |stadium_name= Estadio Brigadier Gral E. López |nickname= El Cementerio de Los Elefantes <br/ > (The Elephants Graveyard) |image= File:Estadio Brigadier General Estanislao López - Colón de Santa Fe.jpg |fullname= Estadio Brigadier General [[Estanislao López]] |location= [[Santa Fe, Argentina|Santa Fe]], [[Argentina]] |built= |opened= 9 July 1946 |tenants= [[Club Atlético Colón]] |seating_capacity= 47,000<ref>http://www.sinmordaza.com/noticia/322168-aca-jugara-colon-union-el-clasico-santafesino.html</ref> |dimensions= }}
'''Estadio Brigadier General Estanislao Lopez''' (nicknamed '''"El Cementerio de Los Elefantes"''') is a [[association football|football]] stadium in [[Santa Fe, Argentina]]. It is the home stadium of [[Club Atlético Colón]]. The stadium has a capacity of 33,458 and was first opened in 1946.<ref name=sway>{{cite web|title=ESTADIO BRIGADIER GENERAL ESTANISLAO LÓPEZ|url=https://int.soccerway.com/venues/argentina/estadio-brigadier-general-estanislao-lopez/|work=Soccerway|publisher=Perform|accessdate=15 March 2015}}</ref>
The ground's nickname (Elephants Graveyard in English) was created in 1964, as a result of the unexpected defeat of the Brazilian team [[Santos FC]] led by [[Pelé]]. The frequent defeats of the major Argentine teams strengthened the reputation.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.futbolred.com/copa-america-2011/noticias/argentina_no_es_bs_as/el-cementerio-de-los-elefantes-el-escenario-de-argentina-colombia/9811644|title= 'El cementerio de los elefantes', el escenario de Argentina-Colombia|trans-title='The Elephants graveyard', the scenario of Argentina-Colombia|language= Spanish|author= Gabriel Briceño|date= |publisher= Fútbol Red|accessdate=July 15, 2014}}</ref>
