{{Infobox stadium | name = Jahnstadion | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = Jahnstadion (Regensburg)- Jahn vs. Unterhaching 2010.jpg | image_size = 300px | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Regensburg]], [[Germany]] | coordinates = {{Coord|49|00|56|N|12|04|26|E|display=inline,title|region:DE-BY_type:landmark}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 1926 | renovated = 1987 | expanded = 1931, 1949, 2003, 2008, 2012 | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Regensburg|City of Regensburg]] | operator = | surface = Grass | estimated_cost = | architect = | capacity = 12,500 | record_attendance = | dimensions = | tenants = [[SSV Jahn Regensburg]] (1926–2015) }}
The '''Jahnstadion''' is a 12,500 capacity [[stadium]] in [[Regensburg]], [[Germany]]. It is primarily used for [[Association football|football]] and, until 2015, was the home of [[SSV Jahn Regensburg]]. Built in 1926, it also hosted five [[Football at the 1972 Summer Olympics|football]] matches during the [[1972 Summer Olympics]].
