{{Refimprove|date=April 2009}}
[[File:Kamui Tips logo.jpg|thumb|Logo of Kamui Tips.]]
'''Kamui Tips''' is a [[Japan]]ese manufacturer of [[Cue stick|cue]] tips for [[Carom billiards|billiards]] and [[Pool (cue sports)|pool]]. According to the company,<ref name="Kamui Brand">[http://www.kamuibrand.com/billiard-en/?page_id=45 Kamui Brand]{{Clarify|date=September 2010|reason=This is not a proper reference citation. Use [[Cite web]] or similar to provide source details.}}</ref> the tips are produced by founder '''Masato Hiraoka''' in his workshop in [[Hiroshima]]. The company and its products are named after the mythological ''[[Kamuy]]''.

Kamui tips first gained international exposure in October 2007, when they were introduced at the [[Billiard Congress of America|BCA]] Super Billiards Expo in the United States. They were endorsed in 2008 by top pro [[Mika Immonen]] as his tip of choice<ref name="NYCGrind.com">[http://nycgrind.com/?p=7571 NYCGrind]{{Clarify|date=September 2010|reason=This is not a proper reference citation. Use [[Cite web]] or similar to provide source details.}}</ref> while winning the [[U.S. Open 9-Ball Championships]] two years in a row, followed by the title of ''Inside Pool Magazine''<nowiki />'s 2009 Player of the Year.<ref name="Inside Pool">[http://www.insidepoolmag.com/magazines/february-2009-insidepool-magazine.html Inside Pool]{{Clarify|date=September 2010|reason=This is not a proper reference citation. Use [[Cite web]] or similar to provide source details.}}</ref>

The tips are made primarily from [[pig leather]], and consist of many layers that are [[Lamination|laminated]] and tempered for a rubber-like consistency. Kamui's process is so specific that some of their products have been in development for more than nine years before they hit store shelves.{{citation needed|date=September 2010}} Currently, Kamui Tips produces two styles of tips: "Kamui Black" and "Kamui".<ref name="Kamui Tips ">"[http://www.kamuitips.com Kamuitips.com]"{{Clarify|date=September 2010|reason=This is not a proper reference citation. Use [[Cite web]] or similar to provide source details.}}</ref> "Kamui Black" tips come in four degrees of hardness: super soft, soft, medium and hard. "Kamui" tips come in four different hardnesses: soft, medium soft, medium and hard.<ref name="Cue Tip Hardness Durometer Test ">[http://www.cuebux.com/tip-hardness-chart.html Tip Hardness Chart]{{Clarify|date=September 2010|reason=This is not a proper reference citation. Use [[Cite web]] or similar to provide source details.}}</ref>

