{{Infobox football club | clubname = Racing Haïtien | image = Racing haitien crest.png | image_size = 130px | fullname = Racing Club Haïtien | nickname = ''Le Vieux Lion''<ref>[http://www.weltfussballarchiv.com/club-profile/haiti/racing-club-ha%C3%AFtien/15308/ Welt Fussball Archiv: Racing Club Haïtien]</ref> | founded = {{start date and age|1923|3|23|df=yes}}<ref>[http://www.haiti-reference.com/loisirs/football/equipes.php Haiti Reference: Le Football Haitien: Équipes et Clubs]</ref><ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haitifound.html Haiti – List of Foundation Dates]</ref> | ground = [[Stade Sylvio Cator]] | coordinates = {{Coord|18|32|9.81|N|72|20|32.79|W|type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | capacity = 15,000<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/article/cwc-final-all-time-results-scorers |title=CWC Final: All-Time Results & Scorers |editor=Press |date=26 October 2014 |publisher=CONCACAF |accessdate=1 February 2016}}</ref> | chairman = | manager = | league = [[Ligue Haïtienne]]<ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesh/haiti2016.html Haiti: Championnat National D1 2016]</ref> | season = [[2016 Ligue Haïtienne season|2016]] | position = Ligue Haïtienne, 14th | website = | pattern_la1=_blueborder|pattern_b1=_navystripes|pattern_ra1=_blueborder|leftarm1=ffff00|body1=ffff00|rightarm1=ffff00|shorts1=000099|socks1=ffff00 }}
'''Racing Club Haïtien''' is a professional [[association football|football]] club based in [[Port-au-Prince]], [[Haiti]]. It is one of the most successful clubs in the country's history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BOwQ82EArigC&pg=PA163&lpg=PA163&dq=RC+Ha%C3%AFtien&source=bl&ots=G9-hm5jJUi&sig=8Kn5a19f_hSeAAb8X4Odo-dvHq4&hl=en&sa=X&ei=7UHQVM2TAuWHsQScnoCoCw&ved=0CDcQ6AEwBzgK#v=onepage&q=RC%20Ha%C3%AFtien&f=false |title=Soccer: The Ultimate Guide |page=163 |publisher=DK Publishing |isbn=9780756663186 |accessdate=2 February 2015}}</ref>
== History == The club has won the most league championships in Haitian club history, 11, winning in 1937-38, 1941, 1946, 1947, 1953-4, 1958, 1962, 1969, 2000, 2002 Clôture and 2009 Clôture. In 1941, it captured [[Double (association football)|the double]] after winning the league and the Coupe d'Haïti.
They are also one of only two Haitian clubs to have ever won the [[CONCACAF Champions' Cup]], along with [[Violette AC]], winning in 1963.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=BOwQ82EArigC&pg=PA163&lpg=PA163&dq=RC+Ha%C3%AFtien&source=bl&ots=G9-hm5jJUi&sig=8Kn5a19f_hSeAAb8X4Odo-dvHq4&hl=en&sa=X&ei=7UHQVM2TAuWHsQScnoCoCw&ved=0CDcQ6AEwBzgK#v=onepage&q=RC%20Ha%C3%AFtien&f=false |title=Soccer: The Ultimate Guide |page=163 |publisher=DK Publishing |isbn=9780756663186 |accessdate=2 February 2015}}</ref>
==Honours== * '''[[Ligue Haïtienne]] (11)''': 1938, 1941, 1946, 1947, 1954, 1958, 1962, 1969, 2000, 2002 C, 2009 C * '''[[Coupe d'Haïti]] (2)''': 1941, 1944 * '''[[CONCACAF Champions' Cup]] (1)''': 1963 * '''Tournoi Haiti-Jamaique-Etats-Unis (1)''': 1968 <ref>[http://www.rsssf.com/tablesd/detcougars-car68.html RSSSF- Detroit Cougars (USA) Caribbean tour 1968]</ref>
